### Test 1: Basic rule instantiation with required attributes

```java
@Test
public void testBasicRuleInstantiation() throws Exception {
    scratch.file(
        "pkg/rules.bzl",
        """
        def _impl(ctx):
            pass
        my_rule = rule(
            implementation = _impl,
            attrs = {
                "src": attr.string(mandatory = True),
            },
        )
        """);
    scratch.file(
        "pkg/BUILD",
        """
        load(":rules.bzl", "my_rule")
        my_rule(
            name = "my_target",
            src = "hello.txt",
        )
        """);
    Package pkg = loadPackage("pkg");
    assertThat(pkg.containsErrors()).isFalse();
    Rule rule = pkg.getRule("my_target");
    assertThat(rule).isNotNull();
    assertThat(RawAttributeMapper.of(rule).get("src", Type.STRING)).isEqualTo("hello.txt");
}
```

